<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Rock Rangers Geology Club</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Rock Rangers Geology Club. A fun school club website for students who love rocks, fossils, minerals, and Earth science." />
  <style>
    :root {
      --bg: #f6f1e8;
      --surface: #fffaf2;
      --card: #ffffff;
      --text: #2f241b;
      --muted: #6e5b4d;
      --accent: #8b5e34;
      --accent-2: #c58b42;
      --line: #e7d7c4;
      --shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(47, 36, 27, 0.08);
      --radius: 18px;
      --max: 1100px;
    }

    * {
      box-sizing: border-box;
    }

    html {
      scroll-behavior: smooth;
    }

    body {
      margin: 0;
      font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
      background: var(--bg);
      color: var(--text);
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    a {
      color: inherit;
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    img {
      max-width: 100%;
      display: block;
    }

    .container {
      width: min(92%, var(--max));
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .topbar {
      position: sticky;
      top: 0;
      z-index: 50;
      background: rgba(255, 250, 242, 0.95);
      backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
    }

    .nav {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: space-between;
      gap: 20px;
      padding: 14px 0;
    }

    .brand {
      font-size: 1.15rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: 0.3px;
    }

    .brand span {
      color: var(--accent);
    }

    .nav-links {
      display: flex;
      gap: 18px;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      color: var(--muted);
    }

    .hero {
      padding: 72px 0 48px;
      background:
        radial-gradient(circle at top right, rgba(197, 139, 66, 0.18), transparent 25%),
        linear-gradient(180deg, #fff7ec 0%, var(--bg) 100%);
    }

    .hero-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1.15fr 0.85fr;
      gap: 34px;
      align-items: center;
    }

    .eyebrow {
      display: inline-block;
      padding: 7px 12px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: #f3e2c9;
      color: var(--accent);
      font-size: 0.84rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }

    h1, h2, h3 {
      line-height: 1.15;
      margin: 0 0 14px;
    }

    h1 {
      font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.8rem);
    }

    h2 {
      font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2.3rem);
    }

    p {
      margin: 0 0 14px;
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 1rem;
    }

    .hero-copy {
      max-width: 640px;
    }

    .cta-row {
      display: flex;
      gap: 12px;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      margin-top: 22px;
    }

    .btn {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 12px 18px;
      font-weight: 700;
      transition: 0.2s ease;
    }

    .btn:hover {
      transform: translateY(-2px);
    }

    .btn-primary {
      background: var(--accent);
      color: #fff;
      border-color: var(--accent);
    }

    .btn-secondary {
      background: var(--surface);
    }

    .hero-card {
      background: var(--card);
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 24px;
      box-shadow: var(--shadow);
      padding: 22px;
    }

    .stone-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
      gap: 14px;
      margin-top: 18px;
    }

    .stone {
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, #fffdf9 0%, #f6ede1 100%);
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 16px;
      padding: 16px;
      min-height: 108px;
    }

    .stone strong {
      display: block;
      margin-bottom: 6px;
      color: var(--text);
    }

    section {
      padding: 64px 0;
    }

    .section-head {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      align-items: end;
      gap: 20px;
      margin-bottom: 22px;
    }

    .cards {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
      gap: 18px;
    }

    .card {
      background: var(--card);
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: var(--radius);
      padding: 22px;
      box-shadow: var(--shadow);
    }

    .card h3 {
      font-size: 1.15rem;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }

    .tag {
      display: inline-block;
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      background: #f6e8d2;
      color: var(--accent);
      padding: 6px 10px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
    }

    .two-col {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 20px;
    }

    .list {
      padding-left: 18px;
      color: var(--muted);
    }

    .list li {
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }

    .gallery {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
      gap: 16px;
    }

    .gallery-item {
      aspect-ratio: 1 / 1;
      border-radius: 20px;
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow);
      padding: 18px;
      display: flex;
      align-items: end;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: #fff;
      background-size: cover;
      background-position: center;
    }

    .g1 { background-image: linear-gradient(rgba(0,0,0,0.15), rgba(0,0,0,0.45)), url('https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1518173946687-a4c8892bbd9f?auto=format&fit=crop&w=800&q=80'); }
    .g2 { background-image: linear-gradient(rgba(0,0,0,0.15), rgba(0,0,0,0.45)), url('https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1469285994282-454ceb49e63a?auto=format&fit=crop&w=800&q=80'); }
    .g3 { background-image: linear-gradient(rgba(0,0,0,0.15), rgba(0,0,0,0.45)), url('https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1441974231531-c6227db76b6e?auto=format&fit=crop&w=800&q=80'); }
    .g4 { background-image: linear-gradient(rgba(0,0,0,0.15), rgba(0,0,0,0.45)), url('https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1473448912268-2022ce9509d8?auto=format&fit=crop&w=800&q=80'); }

    .join-box {
      text-align: center;
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, #fff9f0 0%, #f7ecdd 100%);
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 24px;
      padding: 34px 22px;
      box-shadow: var(--shadow);
    }

    footer {
      border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
      padding: 22px 0 42px;
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }

    @media (max-width: 920px) {
      .hero-grid,
      .cards,
      .two-col,
      .gallery {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      }
    }

    @media (max-width: 700px) {
      .nav {
        flex-direction: column;
        align-items: flex-start;
      }

      .hero-grid,
      .cards,
      .two-col,
      .gallery,
      .stone-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }

      .section-head {
        flex-direction: column;
        align-items: flex-start;
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: 2.3rem;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <header class="topbar">
    <div class="container nav">
      <a href="#home" class="brand">Rock <span>Rangers</span></a>
      <nav class="nav-links">
        <a href="#about">About</a>
        <a href="#activities">Activities</a>
        <a href="#learn">Learn</a>
        <a href="#gallery">Gallery</a>
        <a href="#join">Join</a>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main>
    <section class="hero" id="home">
      <div class="container hero-grid">
        <div class="hero-copy">
          <div class="eyebrow">School Geology Club</div>
          <h1>Dig into the story of the Earth.</h1>
          <p>
            Welcome to Rock Rangers. A fun geology club for students who want to explore rocks, minerals, fossils, volcanoes, maps, and the hidden history under our feet.
          </p>
          <p>
            We learn by doing. We collect samples. We go on field trips. We ask big questions about the planet.
          </p>
          <div class="cta-row">
            <a href="#join" class="btn btn-primary">Join the Club</a>
            <a href="#activities" class="btn btn-secondary">See Activities</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="hero-card">
          <h3>Why students love Rock Rangers</h3>
          <p>Every meeting brings a new Earth science adventure.</p>
          <div class="stone-grid">
            <div class="stone">
              <strong>Rock Hunt</strong>
              Identify local rocks and build your own mini collection.
            </div>
            <div class="stone">
              <strong>Fossil Fun</strong>
              Learn how fossils form and what they tell us.
            </div>
            <div class="stone">
              <strong>Map Skills</strong>
              Read topographic maps and simple field sketches.
            </div>
            <div class="stone">
              <strong>Earth Projects</strong>
              Create models, posters, and club exhibitions.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="about">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-head">
          <div>
            <h2>About the club</h2>
            <p>We make geology exciting, practical, and easy to understand.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="cards">
          <article class="card">
            <div class="tag">Explore</div>
            <h3>See the Earth differently</h3>
            <p>Students learn how rocks form, how land changes, and how Earth processes shape daily life.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="card">
            <div class="tag">Observe</div>
            <h3>Train your eyes</h3>
            <p>We study colour, texture, grain size, layers, crystals, and clues hidden in natural materials.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="card">
            <div class="tag">Create</div>
            <h3>Build real projects</h3>
            <p>Club members make displays, models, charts, sample boards, and science fair work.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="activities">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-head">
          <div>
            <h2>Club activities</h2>
            <p>Simple activities with strong learning value.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="two-col">
          <div class="card">
            <h3>What we do</h3>
            <ul class="list">
              <li>Rock and mineral identification sessions</li>
              <li>Mini field trips around the school environment</li>
              <li>Fossil, volcano, and earthquake lessons</li>
              <li>Soil testing and erosion observation</li>
              <li>Map reading and landform drawing</li>
              <li>Quiz games and exhibition days</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Meeting plan</h3>
            <ul class="list">
              <li>Weekly club meeting after classes</li>
              <li>Monthly outdoor observation task</li>
              <li>Termly project presentation</li>
              <li>Guest talk from a science teacher or field expert</li>
              <li>End of term sample display and awards</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="learn">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-head">
          <div>
            <h2>What students learn</h2>
            <p>Strong foundations for science and geography lovers.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="cards">
          <article class="card">
            <h3>Rocks and minerals</h3>
            <p>Learn igneous, sedimentary, and metamorphic rocks. Study hardness, lustre, streak, and crystal form.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="card">
            <h3>Fossils and past life</h3>
            <p>See how fossils form and how scientists use them to study ancient environments.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="card">
            <h3>Earth forces</h3>
            <p>Understand volcanoes, earthquakes, weathering, erosion, and the movement of tectonic plates.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="gallery">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-head">
          <div>
            <h2>Club gallery</h2>
            <p>Use this section for future club photos and event highlights.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="gallery">
          <div class="gallery-item g1">Field Notes</div>
          <div class="gallery-item g2">Mineral Study</div>
          <div class="gallery-item g3">Outdoor Exploration</div>
          <div class="gallery-item g4">Sample Display</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="join">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="join-box">
          <h2>Join Rock Rangers</h2>
          <p>
            Open to curious students who love science, nature, and hands-on learning.
          </p>
          <p>
            Meeting Day: Every Friday<br>
            Time: 2:00 PM<br>
            Venue: School Science Room
          </p>
          <div class="cta-row" style="justify-content:center;">
            <a href="mailto:geologyclub@yourschool.com" class="btn btn-primary">Contact the Club</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <footer>
    <div class="container">
      Rock Rangers Geology Club. Built for your school community.
    </div>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>
